===Etymology===
From earlier {{etyl|ojp|ja|sort=たべる}} form {{m|ja|食ぶ|tr=tabu||to (humbly) receive or get|pos=from a superior}}, a verb with the {{m|ja|下二段|tr=shimo nidan}} or lower bigrade conjugation pattern. This was the [[humble]] form of {{m|ja|賜ぶ}}, {{m|ja|給ぶ|tr=tabu||to ([[deign]] to) give|pos=to an inferior}}, a verb with the full {{m|ja|四段|tr=yodan}} or quadrigrade conjugation pattern.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref>

Older bigrade ''tabu'' became modern monograde ''taberu'' due to a regular shift in lower bigrade verbs, whereby the older {{m|ja|終止形|tr=shūshikei||terminal form}} ending in ''-u'' was replaced with the {{m|ja|連体形|tr=rentaikei||attributive form}} ending in ''-eru''.

Most likely cognate with {{m|ja|給う|tr=tamau||to give|pos=as a superior gives a thing to, or does something for, an inferior}}.

Compare the historical development of meaning from “to humbly receive” → “to eat”, with the modern use of the humble verb {{m|ja|頂く|tr=itadaku||to receive}} just before eating, in a sense of “I humbly receive this food.”

